broken_parts_comments: All raising mains, football  and rope were very muddy.
The borehole was found nonfunctional at the day of visit
The borehole was abandoned  for more than 5 years.
It was the cylinder the was broken and fell down to the bottom of the borehole.
A damaged cup seal was fished out.

A lot parts were stolen in December 2015 leaving only rising main, cylinder and rubber cone. The villagers have had to rely on the nearest borehole which is at Nakoma primary school, 3kms away. Most of the resorted to drawing water from unprotected wells
It was broken pieces of rod centralisers that were fished out from the bottom of foot valve body.
But the borehole had no flapper hence it was replaced with a new one.
Parts of the borehole were stolen in 2015 leaving only the head case. however they got a donation of rising main pipes and head case cover but the rest of the stolen parts were never recovered.
All the rods were stolen in 2017
No part was replaced on the borehole but the aquagenx turned positive hence the chlorination.
There were no rods in the borehole as they were all stolen in May 2019. Only the hanlldle, footvalve and fulcrum pin were left behind.
No rods were found in the borehole as they together with other parts were stolen in 2016

Clorination did not take place due to high demand for the water at the borehole as community used to rely on tap water but currently they are not functioning. This was reported by Mr. Chikadwewa the one who used to maintain it when it has fault.

This borehole was functional but ecoli test was postive as such the borehole was opened for the clorination purpose only and not any rehabilitation.
This is the reason why there is no picture for the broken parts taken out from the borehole.
The borehole is not chlorinated because the pedestal need welding for it to pump water as all corners of the pedestal were broken.
The borehole is not chlorinated since it has a very poor yield due to very low water table. It is expected that water yield will stabilize as water table rises.
